Fake methamphetamine!  None of this is real, all fake.  Actually a chemical called "isopropylbenzylamine".  Learn how to tell the difference!

heisenbergspecial
127,255 Views•June 30 2017
Select ...
Select ...
See how the light reflects from a crystal face that's as flat as a plane of glass? Real methamphetamine doesn't do this. Sometimes it will be flat on one side from whatever container the crystals were made in, but in that case, it's really obvious. I can't show you the difference with real methamphetamine, since I have none of that.
Select ...
This one too, is very clear, and has some very flat surfaces, also characteristics of isopropylbenzylamine, but not methamphetamine. Ironically, many pictures of "methamphetamine" found with Google Image Search are actually isopropylbenzylamine! This is because that's sometimes what they use to simulate the real thing in shows like Breaking Bad. Even in police photos, there will often be crystals of isopropylbenzylamine, because real methamphetamine is frequently cut with it, and isopropylbenzylamine tends to form large crystals more easily, which photographs better.
Select ...
This piece looks more like real methamphetamine than the other two, even though it isn't. It is, after all, a very good mimic. This is a lesson in why you need to look at as many pieces as possible to spot the telling signs of isopropylbenzylamine.
